## 🛠️ Part 4: Setup Tips

A few things that will dramatically improve quality:

**Give it project context.** The agent gets way better when it knows your stack, conventions, and what "production" means for you. Add a `PROJECT.md` to its knowledge with: language versions, framework, testing approach, deployment target, and 2–3 example "good" PRs.

**Tune the strictness dial.** Add a setting in the system prompt like "Strictness level: HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW" and let users override per request. Greenfield prototypes shouldn't get the same review as payment processing code.

**Add a rubric for approve/request-changes.** Tell it explicitly when to recommend approving vs requesting changes — otherwise it tends to be wishy-washy.

**Feed it your past review comments.** If you can export 20–30 real review comments from your team, that single addition will make it sound like *your* team rather than a generic reviewer.

**Limit scope per call.** Reviews of >500 lines of diff degrade fast. Add an instruction: "If the diff is >500 lines, suggest splitting and review only the most critical file unless the user insists."

